metadata.name: Miniscapes #276
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: menToll #159
metadata.description:
menToll was inspired by a series of OP Art paintings done by Victor Vasarely, called Toll (from the Permutations Series). (c. 1965) Vasarely died in 1997 in the early days of computer art. I'm sure he would have embraced this medium. This is the fifth in a series of Vasarely inspired Generative Art pieces I am offering.

I became interested in Victor Vasarely's graphic artworks while I was in art school. As I struggled to learn computer graphics I wondered how do I write a program to produce imagery with a similar aesthetic? I call the process of creating algorithms inspired by other artists: "Art"ificial Intelligence.

menToll is two layered piece. A 2x2 array of arrays of circles contained within a background square. A similar sized array of squares (with no background of its own) is superimposed and centered on top. Each array of circles with a square has an opacity gradient applied to it allowing its uniquely colored random background to show through its elements. The superimposed top layer of squares is a solid random color.

There are many Gestalt interactions within this piece. Circle groups within each of their containers interact with each other, and their background, in interesting ways. Each new generation with its random color assignments significantly affects your depth perception. The top layer appears to come forward or recede depending on the layer it overlaps. And depending on color combinations there is a variety of "after-imagism" interactions between the squares in the top set. More candy for your mind.

Dr. Bill Generative Art OG @ drbillkolomyjec.com

metadata.name: Seamless Pattern #40
metadata.description:
Generative art piece created with code in Hydra.

A seamless pattern is an image that can be placed side-by-side with copies of itself without any visible seams or interruptions on the content, so you can repeat this image and create a pattern that can go on infinitely to create unique elements. The piece handles different color palettes (around 10) and different geometric patterns.

50% of royalties from this piece go to the development of Hydra Video Synth

by Daniel Oropeza
Panama City, Panama
04/05/2022

metadata.name: Star polygon #11
metadata.description:
"A star polygon {p/q}, with p,q positive integers, is a figure formed by connecting with straight lines every qth point out of p regularly spaced points lying on a circumference." (Wolfram MathWorld)

--------

All NFT's on this platform are about mathematics and this one shows how order can hide under disorder or chaos.
Sometimes, studying mathematics, you can reach some little enlightment when you perfectly understand an important formula.
In that case you can see order where it seemed there was only chaos.

Order and chaos are both fascinating and their combination can be even more interesting, as eastern philosophies teach us, for example.

--------

There are 3 palettes and 9 polygons.

"S" to save 2000x2000 png.

Created by Carla Chicchiero in p5.js
twitter: @sululab
instagram: @sululab
licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0
libreries: none

metadata.name: Symbiosis #47
metadata.description:
Without special effects, the wheat grows in silence, it is meek and humble, but it can feed all of us, if we want to take it with us.

As long as there will be water and light, we will grow wheat, as we have done for thousands of years.
Who knows if it will take the color of the ground on which we will make it grow?
We will make it change and it will change us, in an eternal symbiosis.

---

There are three main backgrounds, with many variations for each background, some of which are nocturnal.
The number of ears can change and eventually a poppy can be found.

"S" to save 2000x2000 png.

metadata.name: Art blocks II #141
metadata.description:
Art Blocks II was built on a dynamic grid system. Blocks with random colors and sizes represent the poetic aesthetics of generative art and the harmony of randomness. This collection is composed of 11 different grid sizes and 4 different patterns of backgrounds with more than 150 color palettes. There will be a roughly 14% chance of getting colorful gradients in the work.

This collection works the best in full size. Enlarge it to see the details :)

- Press "s" to save the image in 4800 × 3200

metadata.name: AngrySquares.gif #3
metadata.description:
An experiment in GIF serialization on fxhash by Nate Donato, this collection features a generative animation that can be automatically saved as a high quality gif.  Playing with block color and simple motion, each iteration features a rapid animation of basic shapes fluctuating under various different constraints.  The combined character of the full animation appears as an "angry" mass with pent up body motion and sharp color contrasting edges.  

Outputs can be programmatically saved to a high quality gif download, which can be used as a unique animated profile picture (*for any service that allows animated gif images)

Featuring:
x10 different possible color schemes (4 with near-infinite variations!)
x4 different possible generative weight classes (each with significant variation)
x3 different accent coloring styles (two with significant variation)
x7 different generalized anger levels (affecting animation speeds)
x6 possible special extra accent detail styles
x5 different base shape constructions
x1 'base' generative algorithm *

= 25,200 possible base feature combinations!!  Some traits and combinations are more likely to appear than others...

* Not included in calculations: a near infinite variety of shape positions, sizes, and placements, and a wide spectrum of possible animation lengths!


--


Keyboard controls:

Press [1] to view at native resolution
Press [2] to view at high resolution
Press [0] to scale to default screen width

Press [S] to save a high quality gif!* (May take a couple seconds to render)

*Tested in Google Chrome browser only!  
Should work in others but please use the latest version of Chrome if encountering any issue.

metadata.name: EYES #193
metadata.description:
The beauty and soul of eyes have always fascinated me. There are billions of eyes in the world, all with different colors, textures and shapes and each one is still unique. With this project, I wanted to capture that natural beauty of the eyes, but also give them my unique colorful style.

Zombie and Cat eyes are more rare. Who will collect the Zombie Cat eye?

----

Created with the help of amazing cables.gl. For optimization purposes, in order to make the project load properly on fxhash, I had to use 2 textures for the eye pupil shapes instead of procedurally generating them. There is also hdr map loaded for the reflections.  

Press E to download the generated image.

----

All who collected NEBULAE were added to the reserve list. <3

metadata.name: Daydreamer #126
metadata.description:
‘For the artist communication with nature remains the most essential condition. The artist is human, himself nature; part of nature within natural space.’ (Paul Klee, 1944) 


Working on long-form nature has an interesting side effect. On the one hand, you're attempting a shallow imitation of a landscape.... You are working with cold logic and code, vainly trying to control randomness to create this virtual facsimile, something you know is artificial.... 

....and yet.... even with all this left-brain activity, your right-brain pushes back, and imagines being there. While working on this project I found myself continually daydreaming, wandering off to hear the sounds of waterfalls, or the crunch of walking along a sandy lake shore. If you've ever wondered about coding, I urge you to learn. Daydreams await....


Press '1' once rendering is finished, to redraw at 5120x5120 resolution 
Press '2' to export without post-processing effects 

3rd party libraries (license text and links included in source) 
- p5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 
- WebGLImageFilter, Dominic Szablewski - phoboslab.org 

I have tried to use soft blurs and shadows to give a sense of layering and depth to the scene. After viewing for a while, it reminds me of 3D paper-art. There are traits for colour and amount of birds, waterfalls, etc. but none are especially rare – These properties are intended for filtering the collection.

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #1297
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: Love #42
metadata.description:
We all experience love at different scales, ranging from scarcely perceived instances of kindness to unforgettable affections shown to us by family and friends, pets and partners. Each of these moments link us to the same boundless and enveloping interconnectedness that persists across space and time: the infinite source of our deepest aspirations.

Like the feeling of simple bliss, ‘Love’ portrays the visceral radiant light and warmth of our innermost joys. By taking a moment to open ourselves up, these swirling worlds of weightless and seemingly infinite brush strokes invite us to slow down and dwell in prismatic intuitive swells.

In doing so, we may find the immense and omnipresent love that needs only our awareness to be felt.

__________

Press 1-9 to load at different scales (1 = 2,000x2,000 (default), 9 = 10,000x10,000)
When zoomed in, once the output is fully loaded, you can click and drag to move around the canvas
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'B' to toggle the background texture on or off
Press 'A' to toggle the loading animation (recommended for very large scales)

Created with p5.js
For third party license information, please see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt
